text: Dorothy Walker Bush Koch,Texas Births, 1926-1995 often called "Doro," (born August 18, 1959), is the daughter of the 41st President of the United States George H. W. Bush and former First Lady of the United States Barbara Bush. Her siblings are George W. Bush, the 43rd President, Jeb Bush, former Governor of Florida, Neil Bush, Marvin Bush, and the late Robin Bush, who died of leukemia in 1953. ==References== Category:1959 births Category:Living people Category:Bush family Category:Children of Presidents of the United States Category:People from Texas Category:George H. W. Bush
title: Dorothy Bush Koch
